es cited by Gauss has been added by the translator. "Whatever set of values is adopted, Gauss's Disquistiones Arithmeticae surely belongs among the greatest mathematical treatises of all fields and periods. . . . The appearance of an English version of this classic is most welcome."-Asger Aaboe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aNumber theory. 7aMATHEMATICS / Number Theory.2bisacsh1 aBressi, Todd W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGroth, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030009473240uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019425840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300194258423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300194258/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY